```java
if (splitStrings.length == 2 &amp;&amp; !splitStrings[1].matches(&quot;(?!0)\\d{1,2}|100&quot;)) {
    throw new IllegalArgumentException(&quot;Invalid Input&quot;);
}
```

[Online demo](https://www.regexplanet.com/share/index.html?share=yyyydqxyjar) of the regexp: `(?!0)\d{1,2}|100` validating _positive_ cases `0 &lt; x &lt;= 100`
* `(?!0)\d{1,2}` - 1 or 2 digit numbers except `0` excluded with negative lookahead `(?!0)`: 1 - 99
* `|100` - OR `100`

